Class TimeSeriesDataProvider

java.lang.Object
fr.ubo.fast.data.provider.service.TimeSeriesDataProvider
@Path("/time-series") public class TimeSeriesDataProvider extends Object
The TimeSeriesDataProvider class represents a service that retrieves time series data from a database.

    • retrieveTimeSeriesData

      @GET @Path("/data/{id}") @Produces("application/json") public String retrieveTimeSeriesData(@PathParam("id") int time_series_id, @QueryParam("start_time") String start_time, @QueryParam("end_time") String end_time, @QueryParam("interval") double interval, @QueryParam("table") String table, @QueryParam("raw") boolean raw)
      This method retrieves from a database the values (raw or min-max) of a given time series over a given time range.
      Parameters:
      time_series_id - : The ID of the time series in the database.
      start_time - : The start time of the time range.
      end_time - : The end time of the time range.
      interval - : The interval over which the min-max is calculated.
      table - : The name of the table which contains the time series.
      raw - : A boolean value that specifies the type of data to retrieve (raw or min-max).
      Returns:
      A formatted string with the retrieved values.
